19/08/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Police in Gjirokastra stopped a truck at the border with Greece on Tuesday (August 18th) which resulted in one arrest and the seizure of 50kg of marijuana. The driver and owner of the truck is believed to be businessman Petrit Abedini, from the nearby town of Tepelena. He ran for mayor as an independent in the February 2007 local elections. (Shekulli, Top News, Balkan Web, Ora News - 18/08/09)
